==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Condyle
<hw>Con"dyle</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>condylus</ets> knuckle, joint, Gr. <grk>ko`ndylos</grk>: cf. F.
<ets>condyle</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A bony prominence;
particularly, an eminence at the end of a bone bearing a rounded
articular surface; -- sometimes applied also to a concave articular
surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Condyloid</ent>⟦br⟧
